title: US state and federal officials clash over fatal Alex Pretti shooting | ABC NEWS
description: Protesters have returned to the streets as federal and Minnesota officials clash over the fatal shooting of 37-year-old nurse Alex Pretti. Pretti was shot by a border force officer while intervening in a confrontation between an immigration officer and a woman on the street. The governor of Minnesota has called it "an inflection point" and urged Donald Trump to withdraw federal immigration agents from the state. title: Victoria prepares for record temperatures as fire risk intensifies | ABC NEWS
description: As Victoria braces for a potential record-breaking heatwave, communities in the Otways and along the surf coast have been told to evacuate as fire threatens the region. The Carlisle River fire breached containment lines on Saturday and residents in towns throughout the Otways, including Forrest, Barwon Downs, Beech Forest, and Barramunga have been told to leave, while coastal communities down the Great Ocean Road have been urged to be on alert. For residents in Gellibrand, it's already been an anxious 24 hours with flames within a kilometre of the town and more challenging conditions ahead. title: Man charged with publicly inciting hatred at March for Australia rally | ABC NEWS
description: A 31-year-old man has been charged after he was arrested at a March for Australia anti-immigration rally in Sydney for alleged hate speech. He was apprehended in Surry Hills after the protest at Moore Park and is charged with publicly inciting hatred on the ground of race causing fear.  The rallies drew thousands nationwide, with some protesting against changing the date of Australia Day and mass immigration. Others expressed support for Neo-Nazi beliefs and made antisemitic remarks. title: Trump administration defends killing man in Minneapolis, contradicts videos | The World | ABC NEWS
description: The Trump administration has again gone on the defensive after another American citizen was fatally shot by immigration agents in Minneapolis. Federal officials allege the victim, Alex Pretti, attacked the officers, labelling him a would-be assassin. title: Myanmar's junta leader dismisses critics as allies head for landslide win | The World | ABC NEWS
description: The final round of voting has now closed in Myanmar in what's been a controversial first general election in the country since a military-backed coup ousted Aung San Suu Kyi in 2021. United Nations officials have labelled the election "illegitimate" as a violent civil war continues to rage across Myanmar. David Mathieson, an independent analyst based in Thailand, tells The World Myanmar's election results were already a foregone conclusion. title: Bangladesh election: Campaigning begins as Sheikh Hasina slams poll in India  | The World | ABC NEWS
description: Campaigning in Bangladesh's election is underway as voters prepare to cast their ballots on the 12th of February. It's also the first election since Sheikh Hasina was ousted from power following a youth-led uprising stemming from a deadly crackdown against anti-government protesters in 2024. So what can we expect from these elections? Dr Mubashar Hasan, an expert on Bangladeshi politics from Western Sydney University spoke to The World's Girish Sawlani about who is likely to emerge victorious.
